- ID providers know your IP address only when register, only one time. It can't continuing track, because it don't need to access ZeroID server when you sign in to other sites.
- ID providers can't lock (revoke) your account. It is ZeroNet designed. So if ZeroID down, new user can't register, but existed user can keep work.

